    • move

      public GameControllerState move​(int workerRow, int workerColumn, int moveRow, int moveColumn, Model gd) throws NotAdjacentCellException, IncorrectLevelException, OccupiedCellException, DomedCellException, DivinityPowerException, NoTurnEndException
      Process the move of a worker
      Parameters:
      workerRow - the row of the cell where the worker is
      workerColumn - the column of the cell where the worker is
      moveRow - the row of the board where the worker wants to move
      moveColumn - the column of the board where the worker wants to move
      gd - the actual game state
      Returns:
      the next controller FSM state
      Throws:
      NotAdjacentCellException - if the destination cell is not adiacent to the worker
      IncorrectLevelException - if the destination cell is too high to be reached
      OccupiedCellException - if the destination cell has another worker on it
      DomedCellException - if the destination cell has a dome on it
      DivinityPowerException - if the move isn't allowed by another divinity
      NoTurnEndException - if the move doesn't allow the player to end the turn

    • build

      public GameControllerState build​(int workerRow, int workerColumn, int buildRow, int buildColumn, Model gd) throws NotAdjacentCellException, OccupiedCellException, DomedCellException, MaximumLevelReachedException, DivinityPowerException
      Process a worker's build action
      Parameters:
      workerRow - the row where the worker is
      workerColumn - the column where the worker is
      buildRow - the row where the player wants to add a level
      buildColumn - the column where the player wants to add a level
      gd - the actual game board state
      Returns:
      the next controller fsm state
      Throws:
      NotAdjacentCellException - if the cell where the player wants to build is not adiacent to the worker's one
      OccupiedCellException - if the destination cell is occupied by another worker
      DomedCellException - is the cell is already domed
      MaximumLevelReachedException - if the cell contains a level 3 building
      DivinityPowerException - if another divinity blocks the increment of the level
